<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2010-06-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Rhinovirus C and Respiratory Exacerbations in Children with Cystic Fibrosis</TITLE><BODY>To investigate a possible role for human rhinovirus C in respiratory exacerbations of children with cystic fibrosis, we conducted microbiologic testing on respiratory specimens from 103 such patients in São Paulo, Brazil, during 2006–2007. A significant association was found between the presence of human rhinovirus C and respiratory exacerbations.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>